7 An Act relating to the Oklahoma School of Science and
Mathematics; appropriating certain funds in certain
8 amount for certain purpose; directing utilization of
certain amounts for certain purposes; providing for
9 noncodification; providing an effective date; and
declaring an emergency.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
14 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
15 There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma School of Science
16 and Mathematics from any monies not otherwise appropriated from the
17 General Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for the fiscal year
18 ending June 30, 2027, the sum of Ninety-three Thousand Dollars
19 ($93,000.00) or so much thereof as may be necessary to perform the
20 duties imposed upon the Oklahoma School of Science and Mathematics
21 by law.
22 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
23 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
24
ENGR. H. B. NO. 4065 Page 1

1 Funds appropriated by Section 1 of this act shall be utilized as
2 follows: Ninety-three Thousand Dollars ($93,000.00) to establish
3 and maintain a School Resource Officer Program or provide physical
4 security enhancements including, but not limited to, school resource
5 officers, cameras, gates, lighting, locks, doors, windows, security
6 geofencing, ballistic storm shelters, and mobile panic alert
7 systems.
8 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
9 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
10 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
11 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
12 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
13 Passed the House of Representatives the 14th day of April, 2026.
